any ideas any has for a fantasy book just lookin suggestions if you are going to write a fantasy book there are a few things you should think about first the first thing would be the setting do you want it to take place in a world that is like the middleages but in a different world like lord of the rings and eragon or do you want it to take place in a modern society like harry potter is it a world with magic if so is it widely accepted dispised or unknown secretive the next thing would be characters are they all human are there different species etc there are lots of things to think about but one of the important things if your world has magic is to set some rules magic can't solve every problem or there would be no plot so it must have limitations that are consistant also try to do something original don't think about what other books did think about what they didn't do what would you like to read in a fantasy book ask yourself these things and write down what you come up with personally i would say to do something fresh try to come up with something completly different but remember that the reader needs to be able to connect with it i hope this has helped you in planning your fantasy Harry Potter High fantasy Fantasy Magic (Harry Potter) Fighting Fantasy Game Books Theory of conduct The Chronicles of Narnia Blood purity (Harry Potter) Fantasy subgenres Immortality Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince Canon (fiction) Fantasy film Science fiction Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film) Swamp Thing Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Sandman (DC Comics Modern Age) Neil Gaiman Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone (film) Hogwarts Dragon Genre fiction Wizard Wizarding world History of fantasy J. K. Rowling Rubeus Hagrid Book of Mormon Carlos Castaneda Magical objects in Harry Potter Fan fiction Eberron Albus Dumbledore Final Fantasy VI Dates in Harry Potter Final F